Boil a full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{0.5%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @Penne Pasta{180%grams} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{260%grams} and sliced pepper. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until the chicken is cooked through and the pepper has softened, ~{8-10%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While everything cooks, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%grams}.

When the chicken and veg have 1 min of cooking time left, add the garlic to the pan and fry until fragrant.

Add the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%grams}, @Chipotle Paste{20%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), @Sugar{1%tsp} for the sauce and @Water{50%ml} for the sauce to the pan.

Stir and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%mins}.

Stir through the @BBQ Sauce{48%grams}, cooked pasta and @Butter{20%grams}. Heat until the pasta is piping hot and the butter has melted, ~{1%min}.

Share the BBQ chicken pasta between your #serving bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the cheese.

Enjoy!